comments.text:
I didn't have money when i was younger and one of my best friends was a 
spoiled brat. every time we would go out to eat i would always say 
McDonalds and he would say no. I wouls say why you just said the other day 
you love McDonalds. He says "I'll never be caught eating their. when i eat 
from their i have someone else go pick up the food". I'm like for real bro? 
i have 3 dollars i can't go anywhere else. weve been through this like 20 
times. either he would ditch me or i would end up going with him and eating 
nothing. and one time. the worst time. he went ahead and paid for me. I 
already felt low. and he made sure to let me know how he was their for me 
when he paid for my food every time we ever got in an argument. as stupid 
and as sad as it sounds. We were best friends for years. but as i got older 
and was forced to be more responsible not growing up with parents or money. 
and as he grew up getting more immature selfish and he wanted to do was 
party we grew apart. and it all started because McDonalds has to be so damn 
cheap. he told me he would eat there if their McDoubles or dollar menu was 
a 3 dollar menu....... It's amazing what people can eventually spite you 
over....Its not my fault i was poor. matter of fact i could go as far to 
say a big reason i didn't have money when i was friends with him was 
because of him. I had a job and got him a job at the same place. I'll be 
damned if he forgot to pick me up and i lost my job. and when he brought up 
him paying for my food i brought up getting him his job he said "wow your a 
self centered piece of shit I helped you in your time of need and i didnt 
even need the job so it doesn't count." in yet 3 years later he is still 
working there....﻿
